APP NAME (WORKING): DockWalker

CORE THESIS
DockWalker is a hyper-focused, two-sided, real-time daywork hiring app for the superyacht industry. It exists to eliminate friction in short-term crew hiring (1–14 day engagements), especially for green crew entering the industry, while remaining fully usable for experienced crew.

It is NOT a full-time hiring marketplace.
It is NOT a reputation scoring system.
It is NOT a social network.
It is NOT a vessel management system.
It is NOT a gamified career app.
It is NOT a long-term contract platform.

It is a fast, structured, low-friction dispatch layer for maritime professionals seeking daywork oportunities.

------------------------------------------------------------
1. USERS
------------------------------------------------------------

USER TYPES:
- Crew (green + experienced)
- Employer (Captain, Chief Engineer, Bosun, HOD, Management rep)
- Dual-role users allowed (crew who can also post)

CREW CHARACTERISTICS:
- Often dockwalking
- Frequently changing availability
- Limited formal CV structure
- High sensitivity to time and cash flow
- Cannot "post a job" as the "crew" variant of their profile

EMPLOYER CHARACTERISTICS:
- Time constrained
- Needs short-term cover urgently
- Wants structured filtering
- Risk aware but pragmatic
- Cannot "apply for job" as the "employer" variant of their profile

Crew can act as employers (crew-crew hiring circumstances), employers cannot act as crew (apply).

