4. CORE EXPERIENCE FLOW
------------------------------------------------------------

CREW SIDE (TINDER-LIKE MECHANIC)

A. Job Discovery:
- One job shown at a time.
- Swipe Right type of mechanic = Apply.
- Swipe Left type of mechanic = Pass.
- Tap = View full structured details.

Job Card Fields:
- Vessel size (exact length or length band)
- Vessel type (private/charter/NDA)
- Role needed
- Duration (start date + end date + working days count)
- Location (limited to granularity level of region, (med/Caribbean etc) city and port/marina
- Day rate (optional but encouraged)
- Required certs
- Experience bracket
- Meals provided (breakfast/lunch/dinner/combination of any)
- Special notes

B. Apply:
- Single tap confirmation after initial application CTA.
- Structured profile auto-attached.
- Optional 250-char message with application.
- No CV uploads required.

C. Application State:
- Applied
- Viewed
- Rejected (neutral/non-shaming)
- Accepted
- Cancelled
- Completed

D. Messaging:
- Opens ONLY after employer accepts.
- No auto-deletion.
- No disappearing messages.
- All messages retained "on server" (append only) unless removed by the user (UI level/one sided).

------------------------------------------------------------

EMPLOYER SIDE (use the same fields between post daywork and viewed daywork card)

A. Post Daywork:
Fields:
- Role
- Location
- Duration
- Start date
- Vessel size band
- Required certs
- Experience bracket
- Optional rate
- Optional notes

B. Applicant Stack (Tinder-style)
- One applicant at a time.
- Swipe Right = Accept.
- Swipe Left = Reject.
- Tap = Full structured profile.

Applicant View:
- Role history summary
- Certifications
- Availability status
- Location proximity
- Past daywork count (no rating)
- Experience duration bands

C. Accept:
- State change → Confirmed.
- Messaging auto-opens.

